{
  "stem": "27509.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In the old-- in those days, they were two-storied sideboards with glass-inlaid windows in the-- in the-- in the doors and so on.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He looked at it and didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Coming from Russia, he hasn't seen it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He-- he didn't know what it was, and he-- and-- and he wrote down that it is a wardrobe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He just didn't know what it was.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he wrote it all down, and then he turned round to us and said to us, you can [? live ?] here, but remember, this furniture is not yours anymore.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It belongs to the state.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And that worker out of [INAUDIBLE] signed the protocol, and that was the end of-- of that story.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The money situation with the arrival of the Russians was momentarily rather extraordinary, as I mentioned before, because suddenly with the-- everybody knew that in Russia there is a surfeit of money and a shortage of goods.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So as it is generally in wartime, you know, there is a story-- there is a joke being said about the difference between war and peace-- that in peacetime you keep the money in the safe and the goods on the shelf, in wartime you keep the money on the shelf and the goods in the safe.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that-- that is exactly how it was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People bought everything because suddenly everybody had money suddenly.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they bought things so irrationally, so absurdly, because--",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Such as?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My own uncle, the clever, intelligent, brilliant man, brilliant man-- you would give him-- you would tell him, 3,745 and 3/4 yards of material at 3 and 3/4 kopeks.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How much would it be?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He would write it down.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "This sort of a brain.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
